---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Terms & Conditions — Code & Blocks"
  description="Terms and conditions for Affiliate Blocks for Amazon — refund policy, subscriptions, lifetime license, and support."
  canonical="/terms"
  lang="en"
  altHref="/de/agb"
>
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container" style="max-width:720px;">
      <h1 style="color:var(--color-white);font-size:2rem;margin-bottom:.5rem;">Terms &amp; Conditions</h1>
      <p class="text-muted" style="margin-bottom:2.5rem;">Last updated: March 2026</p>

      <div class="legal-body">

        <h2>1. General</h2>
        <p>
          These Terms &amp; Conditions apply to all purchases and licenses of plugins and digital products
          sold by Marijan Kelava trading as Code &amp; Blocks (<a href="https://codeandblocks.xyz">codeandblocks.xyz</a>).
          By completing a purchase you agree to these terms.
        </p>

        <h2>2. 14-Day Money-Back Guarantee</h2>
        <p>
          If you are not satisfied with your purchase for any reason, you may request a full refund
          within <strong>14 days</strong> of the original purchase date — no questions asked.
        </p>
        <p>
          To request a refund, simply send an e-mail to
          <a href="mailto:marijan@codeandblocks.xyz">marijan@codeandblocks.xyz</a> with your order
          number. Refunds are processed within 5 business days via the original payment method.
        </p>
        <p class="text-muted" style="font-size:.9rem;">
          The money-back guarantee does not apply to renewals — only to the initial purchase.
        </p>

        <h2>3. Subscription Plans</h2>
        <p>
          Subscription plans (e.g. Personal Monthly, Professional Monthly) are billed on an
          <strong>annual basis</strong>. Each subscription period covers <strong>12 months</strong>
          of plugin updates and support from the date of purchase.
        </p>
        <p>
          Subscriptions do <strong>not</strong> renew automatically. When your subscription period
          ends, you will receive a renewal notice. Renewing for another year extends your updates
          and support for a further 12 months at the then-current price.
        </p>
        <p>
          If you choose not to renew, the plugin continues to work as installed, but you will no
          longer receive new feature updates, bug fixes, or support.
        </p>

        <h2>4. Lifetime License</h2>
        <p>
          The <strong>Personal Lifetime</strong> license grants you access to all updates and
          bug fixes released within the current major version series (<strong>3.x</strong>).
          This means every 3.x release is included at no extra cost for as long as that version
          is actively maintained.
        </p>
        <p>
          When a new major version is released (e.g. <strong>4.x</strong>), the lifetime license
          does <strong>not</strong> automatically include it. At that point you have two options:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Continue using your current 3.x version indefinitely — it keeps working.</li>
          <li>Upgrade to the new major version at a <strong>special discounted upgrade price</strong>
              available exclusively to existing lifetime customers.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          The lifetime license is valid for use on an unlimited number of your own websites
          (personal or client sites, according to your plan tier).
        </p>

        <h2>5. Support</h2>
        <p>
          Support is included for the duration of an active subscription or lifetime license.
          For subscription plans, support covers the same 12-month period as the plan itself —
          renewing your subscription renews your support access.
        </p>
        <p>
          Support is provided via e-mail at
          <a href="mailto:marijan@codeandblocks.xyz">marijan@codeandblocks.xyz</a>.
          Professional plan subscribers receive priority support with faster response times.
        </p>

        <h2>6. License Usage</h2>
        <p>
          Plugin licenses are for use on sites you own or manage. You may not resell, redistribute,
          or sublicense the plugin or any part of it. Each license tier has a specific product limit
          (number of products in the library) as described on the
          <a href="/affiliateblocks#pricing">pricing page</a>.
        </p>

        <h2>7. Changes to These Terms</h2>
        <p>
          We reserve the right to update these terms at any time. Material changes will be
          announced via the plugin's changelog or by e-mail. Continued use of the plugin after
          a change constitutes acceptance of the updated terms.
        </p>

        <h2>8. Contact</h2>
        <p>
          Questions about these terms? Reach out at
          <a href="mailto:marijan@codeandblocks.xyz">marijan@codeandblocks.xyz</a>.
        </p>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
.legal-body {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  gap: 1rem;
  color: var(--color-muted);
  line-height: 1.75;
}
.legal-body h2 {
  color: var(--color-white);
  font-size: 1.15rem;
  font-weight: 700;
  margin-top: 1.5rem;
  margin-bottom: .25rem;
}
.legal-body p,
.legal-body ul {
  margin: 0;
}
.legal-body ul {
  padding-left: 1.4rem;
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  gap: .4rem;
}
.legal-body a {
  color: var(--color-accent);
}
.legal-body strong {
  color: var(--color-text);
}
</style>
